title: Coronavirus: What do all the terms mean?
description: Use our tool to check the meaning of key words and phrases associated with the Covid-19 outbreak
content:
• Asymptomatic A person who has a disease but is displaying no symptoms of that illness. A study of one village in Italy suggests 50-75% of Covid-19 cases there could be asymptomatic.
